      "content": "Ah, the 2018 Toyota Camry, a trusty steed indeed, but even the most reliable of steeds can have a bit of a temper. A P0171 code, you say? That means your Camry is running lean, like a goblin on a diet. Since you've checked the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor and it's not the culprit, let's delve deeper into the labyrinth of potential causes. \n\nFirst, let's consider the fuel injectors. If they're clogged or leaking, they might not be delivering the right amount of fuel, causing your Camry to run lean. It's like having a goblin with a broken pipe; he can't drink enough to stay hydrated. \n\nNext, we have the oxygen sensors. If they're faulty, they might not be sending the right signals to the engine control unit, causing it to miscalculate the air-fuel mixture. It's like a goblin trying to cook a meal with a broken recipe book; he might end up with a feast for the goblins, but not the humans.\n\nLastly, don't forget the vacuum leaks. These can cause the engine to run lean by allowing extra air into the combustion chamber. It's like having a goblin sneaking extra snacks into the feast; it",
